      "content": "hey, can u look at these logs? we're seeing some weird p99 spikes in the payment-gateway microservice during peak hours. mostly intermittent.\n\n{\"timestamp\": \"2023-10-27T14:02:01.452Z\", \"service\": \"payment-gateway\", \"latency_ms\": 45, \"status\": 200, \"db_conn_wait\": 0.002}\n{\"timestamp\": \"2023-10-27T14:02:02.110Z\", \"service\": \"payment-gateway\", \"latency_ms\": 1240, \"status\": 200, \"db_conn_wait\": 1.150}\n{\"timestamp\": \"2023-10-27T14:02:03.005Z\", \"service\": \"payment-gateway\", \"latency_ms\": 42, \"status\": 200, \"db_conn_wait\": 0.001}\n{\"timestamp\": \"2023-10-27T14:02:04.890Z\", \"service\": \"payment-gateway\", \"latency_ms\": 980, \"status\": 200, \"db_conn_wait\": 0.980}\n{\"timestamp\": \"2023-10-27T14:02:05.120Z\", \"service\": \"payment-gateway\", \"latency_ms\": 38, \"status\": 200, \"db_conn_wait\": 0.002}\n\nthe spikes seem to correlate with the db_conn_wait going up. any ideas what we should check first?",
